Not at all. In this case, by &#x27;languages without braces&#x27; we mean languages where indentation is part of the grammar. Python&#x27;s grammar includes explicit INDENT/DEDENT tokens. It is impossible to reindent this mangled python:<p><pre><code>    if z:
    print &#x27;a&#x27;
    print &#x27;b&#x27;</code></pre>
